gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 121, Mavericks 87
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Mavericks, 121-87. Karl-Anthony Towns recorded a game-high 29 points (4-6 3pt. FG), along with nine rebounds and four assists for the Timberwolves, while Rudy Gobert added 17 points and six rebounds in the victory. Josh Green (18 points) and Jaden Hardy (15 points) combined for 33 points for the Mavericks in the losing effort. The Timberwolves improve to 34-14 on the season, while the Mavericks fall to 26-22.
